Jeroen van Oorschot 2013

domo.py is the file that runs continuously to check for changed settings. It is mostly used to play radio.
alarm.py is called every minute by crontab to check if any clock related setting should change
logging.py is called every half hour to log measured values

index.php is the landing page for any user
settings.php is the page where settings can be changed, or loggings can be read
loadPage.php loads and builds a whole page from the database and sends the html as json string to settings.php
loadValues.php gets all the values of the settings from the database and sends them to settings.php to keep the values there up to date

login.php is used to create a session for a remote user, local users are automatically allowed
checkLevel.inc checks if a session or users is still valid
color.inc reads the users preffered color from the database

tree.php shows the database structure
